Athenaeus Dor-cors ac Dinner [on the voracity of Alcman]: And in his fifth Book he shows his gluttony thus:

And seasons made he three, summer and winter and the third the autumn, and a fourth also, to wit the spring, when things do Hourish and grow but one cannot eat his fill.
